snippet.textDisplay:
I had a roommate like Amber, and the words that she spoke in that recording hit home for me. It was nothing but gaslighting from this woman, who thought she owned the house even though she was still paying everyone’s rent to the landlord or so we all thought. She would get into truly aggressive, passive aggressive fights about legitimately anything regarding her, yourself or a problem with “her” house that would quickly turn into nasty yelling and screaming and crying argument every single time complete with emasculating observations and truly degrading comments made to not just weaken her victim but to cripple them in an argument so she can always win without listening to a single word of conflict at hand. There were also sometimes threats of physical violence and when you brought this up, she would double down and become mentally abusive saying, “how dare you, i am a woman, i would never do any of this I’m only saying it cause you made me mad and the fact that you’re scared of me hurts me and it just goes to show how much of a man you really are.” These comments were always regarding something personal and told in confidence and she would use it, flip the script and gun you down with it as her personal ammunition. There were times where one of our other roommates did one tiny little thing like leave the facet just dripping and she would bang on our doors and scream at the top of her lungs for people to turn it off and clean the house. When we would refuse in fear of being screamed at, she would threaten our rent and would tell the roommates that weren’t paying immediately in full that they would need to pay her double every day they wouldn’t pay through group text. I moved out as soon as I could and when she asked me to pay her an absorbent amount of money for the one day I was there to move my stuff out, even though i told her months ago that i was moving on that specific day, and when I stood my ground since i didn’t owe her anything even telling her to check the receipts and send them to me, she threatened to take me to court. I said go ahead and blocked her on everything but my poor roommates the next few weeks were mentally tortured by her, calling me every day to tell me about it. She even called the cops on my roommates claiming that they were intruders in the house and they needed to be dealt with. She even threatened my roommates son. What she did in that house to all of us has left a mental scar on me forever. She got her way to the very end when the landlord finally found out that she was pocketing all of our rent money and spending it on either adderall or god knows what else and purposefully keeping the house in red.

Not only do these stories need to be told, but they need to be heard by everyone to be taken seriously. Not just women, but people like this need to be stopped. And this is not a one way street. Men get abused both mentally and physically by women and it’s our societal stigma that has blinded us from these aggressive tendencies. If you’re a man that has been abused by a women, it is okay and valid to speak up and share your stories, it’s time to start living in the sunlight and not be afraid of these people anymore and the power that they had.
